description: Twisted Tomorrows: Part 3 of 3. Guest-starring Nick Fury and the Falcon. During the waning days of World War II, Cap lost his first partner, Bucky, when they attempted to stop a missile which was heading for the American capitol. History threatens to repeat itself as the villainous Hatemonger has chained the Falcon and an American hero to two warheads, and he's just launched them. Can Captain America and Nick Fury somehow stop these missiles and save their friends before they reach American soil thus kicking off World War III?
name: Twisted Tomorrows, Part 3

description: "Grotesqueries!" Part 1 of 4. Guest-starring Thor and Nick Fury. Sharon Carter has gone missing in one of the most dangerous places in the Marvel U, the prehistoric Savage Land! When Cap ventures to the land that time forgot he soon discovers one of the most notorious villains from the Avengers' rogues gallery has seemingly returned from the grave. Plus, A.I.M. uncovers a dark secret from the early days of the super-soldier program.
name: Grotesqueries

description: "The Savage Man!" Part 2 of 4. Guest-starring Ka-Zar. Captain America has arrived in the prehistoric Savage Land in search of his missing ex-girlfriend and S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent 13, Sharon Carter. But the Sentinel of liberty has discovered that there is more amiss here then he at first realized. Someone is performing bizarre experiments on the denizens of the Land, and its protector, Kevin Plunder, a.k.a. Ka-Zar, has been inexplicably aged. Cap will be shocked to learn who's behind it all.
name: The Savage Man

description: "Waste of Dreams." Guest-starring Ka-Zar. The villain behind the strange happenings in the Savage Land stands revealed and it's none other than the Avengers villain, Count Nefaria. Previously thought dead, the malevolent Count has returned to achieve that which has so far eluded him - World Domination! Only the Sentinel of Liberty has a hope of stopping him now, but can even Captain America survive against an adversary who has singlehandedly fought the Mighty Avengers to a stand still? Meanwhile, A.I.M. awakens the slumbering Protocide.
name: Waste of Dreams

description: "Hidden Paths." Guest-starring Ka-Zar. Reunited with Sharon Carter, Captain America and Agent 13 try desperately to reverse the damage done to the fauna of the Savage Land by Count Nefaria. Plus, Steve and Sharon finally come to an understanding about their turbulent relationship.
name: Hidden Paths

description: "Heart!" Guest-starring Sgt. Fury and the Howling Commandos. Relive an adventure from the harrowing days of World War II with Captain America, Sgt. Fury, and the Howling Commandos.
name: Heart

description: A.I.M. (Advanced Idea Mechanics) has been hounding the Sentinel of Liberty for months now. They even resurrected a forgotten super-soldier experiment gone wrong to murder the stalwart Avenger, but now Cap strikes back. But the identity of A.I.M.'s leader will shock him to his very core.
name: A Gulf So Wide

description: Captain America has finally toppled the leader of A.I.M. The only problem is that their leader is none other then Connie's missing brother. Connie, the woman Steve Rogers has been dating for months now. Connie, the lawyer who plans to discredit Captain America and get all charges against her brother dropped. Connie, the woman who loves Steve Rogers, but despises Captain America. This one gets complicated kiddies.
name: Fighting Back

description: Batroc the Leaper has been hired by an unknown employer to obtain the US launch codes for its nuclear arsenal. If Captain America can't stop his erstwhile sparring partner from getting these codes to this mysterious benefactor freedom may just become a thing of the past.
name: Duel

description: Is even Captain America a match for the walking WMD known as Crimson Dynamo. To save the life of his friend Nick Fury, he'll have to be.
name: Fractured

description: Cap and Nick Fury have been captured on the wrong side of the Iron Curtain. Outgunned and outnumbered can these two old warhorses manage to take down Iron Man's part-time sparring partner, Crimson Dynamo, and a madman who wants to take over the world?
name: Candor

description: Steve reveals his secret identity to Connie, further complicated their already rocky relationship. Plus, Captain America goes toe-to-toe with one of the deadliest men alive - Taskmaster!
name: Conclusions

description: As heroes gather for a funeral for a friend, they relive the recent days' events which led them here. The nefarious Red Skull had hijacked the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier and obtained launch codes for the US's nuclear arsenal (see X-Men Annual (1999) and Captain America (1998 3rd Series) #41 respectfully). The only thing that could stop this madman from starting WW III was the Sentinel of Liberty. But, was this Cap's last hooray? Who else's funeral could draw together prominent members of S.H.I.E.L.D. and the super-hero community?
name: America Lost, Part 1

description: As more and more heroes and friends arrive to pay their respects to a fallen friend, the details of Cap's last adventure continue to unfold. At last, with help from Iron Man, Captain America has located the hijacked S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier, but is he too late to stop the Red Skull from starting World War III?
name: America Lost, Part 2

description: As Cap battles the Red Skull aboard the hijacked S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier, tensions continue to escalate across North America. Can the Sentinel of Liberty prevail against seemingly insurmountable odds yet again, or will America tear itself apart at the seems?
name: America Lost, Part 3

description: Can Captain America prevent hate and intolerance from ruling the day, or will the American Dream perish under the iron boots of the deadly duo of the Red Skull and the Hatemonger? Has the Sentinel of Liberty won all those battles only to lose the war to his most hated adversary? After all, this tale is being told in the past tense from a funeral for a hero.
name: America Lost, Part 4

description: After his friend Sam Wilson (a.k.a. the Falcon) helps him reach an epiphany, Steve visits Connie and Sharon Carter to settle, once and for, all the emotional baggage between them all.
name: Closure

description: 'Nuff Said! Special Double-Size Final Issue. "Silent Night, Silent Morning!" Story by Dan Jurgens. Art by Dan Jurgens and Bob Layton. In this all silent Christmas tale, a down on his luck family man helps the Sentinel of Liberty survive an encounter with the always dangerous Absorbing Man. And by stories end a bonafide Christmas Miracle occurs. Includes the 4-page script for this story. "Keep in Mind!" Story by Kathryn Kuder. Art by Stuart Immonen. Steve Rogers reflects on his time in the War. "To the Core!" Story by Dan Jurgens. Cap brings Sharon Carter to a hidden S.H.I.E.L.D. training facility to show her just how much she means to him. Featuring key moments from Cap's past as rendered by such artists as Dan Jurgens, Bob Layton, John Romita, Sr., Bruce Timm, Ron Frenz, Rick Veitch, Tom Palmer, Sal Buscema, Mike Zeck, and Al Gordon. "Relics!" Story by Brian David-Marshall. Art by Igor Kordy. Late one night, Captain America is summoned for a midnight mission. But this latest case quickly turns into a fight for his life. "A Moment of Silence!" Story by Jen Van Meter. Art by Brian Hurtt and Jim Mahfood. As a nation mourns the passing of a true American icon, one little boy takes the loss of his hero especially hard. "Stars and Stripes Forever!" Story by Evan Dorkin. Art by Kevin Maguire. Captain America's friends and enemies alike elegies him. Featuring appearances by nearly every inhabitant of the Marvel Universe. Story continues in Captain America: Dead Men Running. Includes a 4-page sneak preview of Captain America: Dead Men Running #1.
name: Silent Night, Silent Morning; Keep In Mind; To The Core; Relic; A Moment Of Silence; Stars And Stripes Forever

description:
In the aftermath of 9/11, Cap must deal with the way America - and the world - have changed. From the ruins of the World Trade Center to the horrors of a small town shaken by terrorism, this is one double-sized first issue you'll never forget - and neither will Marvel's star-spangled champion. Said Rieber: "The man's a soldier: fierce, focused, and absolutely dedicated to the American dream." He fights for the people - we, the people. Because he's one of us. He knows this country. He sees America as it is - the beauty and the bloody shadows of it, the nobility and the savagery of it. He knows what it could be - what it should be. What it was meant to be, from the beginning... and he'd die to get us there. He is the shield. Liberty's shield. And though he's just a man, like the ideal of freedom that drives him, he's really hard to kill." Said Cassaday: "I can't say this will be a revolution or an unrecognizable Captain America. However, what John Ney Rieber and I are putting together will deliver a Captain America that has more on his mind than beating the super-villain-of-the-week senseless. Our Cap believes in the American standard, but you won't catch him delivering syrupy speeches. Our man's patriotic testosterone comes out of his angry fists, not endless rhetoric. He fights for the American dream, fearing he'll never have the chance to experience it himself. Revolution? Maybe not. But it is The New Deal."

After 9/11, Captain America digs through the ruins of the World Trade Center to find survivors. Nick Fury wants him to fly to Afghanistan, which makes Cap angry because he feels he is needed in his home country.

Wandering through New York, he feels the world has changed. A young Arab American is attacked at night on the streets and saved by Cap, who also helps the attackers to understand that they have to be strong.

In a town called Centerville some kind of weapons are dropped from the sky. Cap flies in, finding a deserted town. He needs to save its people.
name: Enemy, Chapter One: Dust

description: Captain America tackles terrorism on the home front! Marvel Knights is proud to present an all-new, ongoing CAPTAIN AMERICA series of gut-wrenching intensity, by the acclaimed creative team of writer John Ney Rieber (Books of Magic) and penciler John Cassaday (Planetary)! A small town in America -- seized by the international terrorist called Shaytan! And in the wake of 9/11, the Super Soldier must make some hard decisions about his role in the world!
name: Enemy, Chapter Two: On Nation
Who Will Be The Master of the Soul Gem?  Continuing the Hunt for Gemini
Rune vs. the Vengeance of Gemini.  Only one will walk away!

description: Matt is angry and depressed, contemplating suicide, but decides to hunt down the man responsible for Karen's death, the man who hired Bullseye. After some persuasive questioning he knows where to find him. When he gets there he fights men pretending to be the Hand. Then he climbs up the elevator shaft which is filled with torchered souls, including a Karen look-a-like, but it does have the same heartbeat as her. He continues making his way through the building, revealing the truths of the oddities experienced in recent days. Finally, He gets to the top and meets the man responsible for everything; Mysterio.
name: Guardian Devil Part 6: The Devil Divested

description: It is revealed the one responsible for the entire conspiracy is Mysterio. Before Daredevil can beat him senseless, Mysterio reminds him that he has the baby and it is inside an airtight chamber, with twenty minutes to live. He then begins to ramble on about all his accomplishments and how the world has not given him the recognition he deserved. The reason for his most recent ploy is revealed to be a tumor, and it was killing him, so he wanted a dramatic demise. He felt that Daredevil was like him, a second stringer and a worthy foe. So he created a scenario that would undo him. He revealed how he faked the virgin pregnancy and the girl's vision, how he drugged Foggy and framed him for murder and faked Karens positive HIV results. Daredevil no longer wants to listen, so he deactivates Mysterio's suit, but doesn't kill him like Mysterio wants and Mysterio kills himself. Daredevil then finds the baby and leaves the building.
name: Guardian Devil Part 7: The Devil's Demon

description: The issue begins on the day of Karen Page's funeral and many are in mourning, but none more so than Matt. He has no words to express his sorrow at her funeral. In her will she left him a large sum of money on the condition he will spend it on himself. Later, he meets Spider-Man on the Brooklyn Bridge, and Spider-Man tries to console him with the experience of his own loss, and it helps. Matt then goes to Natasha's place and explains what happened, and asks for her forgivness for his foolishness, which he recieves. Later in the day he and Foggy go to the old lot where he used to live and Matt says they are going to open their own law firm using the money from Karen. The next morning, Matt is at the hospital and is told that the baby is going to be adopted, he is given the opportunity to name her and he decides on Karen.
name: Guardian Devil Part 8: The Devil's Deliverance

description: Matt returns to his office turmed crime-scene, and later meets Maya who wants to talk to him the next day in regards to Wilson Fisk. That night, Daredevil breaks into Fisk's tower and steals his files, leaving only allowing the gun to remain. Fisk, knowing who did it, goes to Maya and tells her he knows who killed her father; Daredevil. She swears vengeance on him, but what she doesn't know is that Fisk killed her father.
name: Parts of a Hole Part 2: Echoes!'

description: Determined to avenge her father, Maya watches videos of Daredevil and his fighting style, meanwhile Matt finds out his deceased client was actually the twin brother of the person with the information. He then goes to have coffee with Maya. They get along well, and greatly enjoy each others company. That night, while Daredevil is on patrol, he is attacked by Maya, who is able to mimic his moves and the moves of his enemies. They never stay still long enough for her to read his lips, so Daredevil is unable to stop the fight. After a careless move on his part, she gets the upper hand and points the gun that killed her father at his head.
name: Parts of a Hole Part 3: Dinner & A Movie

description: During the fight between Daredevil and Maya, now going by Echo, they were responsible for several good deeds. They stop a man from raping a nineteen year old girl, the man lands on a car and stop a man from committing suicide by shooting himself in the car, the noise distracts some neighbor hood punks killing each other, and a cop, whose partner was killed, comes out of his catatonic state when the rapist, who killed the cop's partner, is captured outside his window.
name: Parts of a Hole Part 4: Gun Play
Parts of a Hole Part 5: Trial and Error
Parts of a Hole Part 6: An Object In Motion
Parts of a Hole The Conclusion: Vision

description: Leap frog has a son. He`s autistic. And interested in DD.
name: Wake Up Part One
Wake Up Part Three

description: Daily Bugle reporter Ben Urich confronts Daredevil about a crucial battle from his past — while the life of a little boy hangs in the balance! How is the Man Without Fear connected to a child he doesn't know?
name: Wake Up Part Four

description: When a rich man decides to sue Daredevil for property damage, he hires Matt Murdock as his attorney. Wait a minute, Matt Murdock is Daredevil! So how can the Man Without Fear be in two places at once? Plus: a very special back-up tale that guest-stars Spider-Man, is penciled by legendary DD artist Gene Colan, and is scripted by none other than Stan Lee! ?
name: Playing to the Camera Part One: Redsuit Lawsuit

description: The Jester is out of jail ? and someone's hired him to deliver a nasty message! So what's his connection to the case that has Matt Murdock prosecuting his own alter-ego? The Jester might be laughing, but Daredevil sure isn't!
name: Playing to the Camera Part Two: A Fellow of Infinite Jest

description: It's the strangest legal case of the century: lawyer Matt Murdock vs. his alter ego, Daredevil! If he's going to defend himself against, well, himself, DD needs a lawyer... but it's Murdock himself who may have to settle!
name: Playing to the Camera Part Three: Legal Questions

description: Attorney Matt Murdock is forced to prosecute his secret identity, Daredevil ? but he's convinced that someone may have framed them both! So is there really an old enemy behind it all ? or something even stranger?
name: Playing to the Camera Part Four: Making Offers

description: Matt Murdock vs. Daredevil! The trial begins! DD struggles to unravel the conspiracy against him ? but it's time for his alterego, Matt Murdock, to prosecute the case! How can they both appear in court at once ? and who's behind it all? Best of all, this summer spectacular written by Bob Gale ("Back to the Future", Batman: No Man's Land) concludes in just two weeks in DAREDEVIL #25!
name: Playing to the Camera: Ruminations Over Manhattan

description: The mastermind behind Daredevil's courtroom woes ? revealed at last! "Playing to the Camera" concludes as DD squares off in court against his own alterego, Matt Murdock! Even if he wins, he loses ? but can he get to the bottom of it all before the jury renders its verdict?
name: Playing to the Camera Part Six: Who is the Masked Man?

description: You dug his four-issue examination of Ben Urich -- now Bendis fixes his microscope directly on Daredevil! What happens inside Matt Murdock when he pulls on the crimson mask? And when the human bomb named Nitro attacks, is the Man without Fear also the Man without Mercy? Plus: who is Mr. Silk -- and what does his appearance mean for the Kingpin?
name: Underboss: Part One

description:
Overview

His name is Silke -- and he's determined to unseat the Kingpin from his throne! And his actions have already begun to unhinge Daredevil, who's losing control of his behavior! The red-hot team of Brian Michael Bendis and Alex Maleev (Sam & Twitch) bring a bold new look and feel to Marvel Knights' flagship character!
name: Underboss: Part Two

description: It's The Man Without Fear ? or words! There's a bounty on Daredevil's head, and everyone's out to kill him -- but only one person might be able to do the job. Plus: DD receives a message from his old flame, the sexy assassin known as Elektra! "Underboss," the new epic by the red-hot creative team of Eisner and Wizard Fan Award-Winner Brian Michael Bendis and Alex Maleev (Superman Vs. Predator), continues with a silent twist!
name: Underboss: Part Three

description: Vanessa Fisk, wife of the Kingpin of Crime, is back ? and she's determined to find out who's done horrible things to her husband. And what's the connection between Silke and Matt Murdock? The net draws tighter around Daredevil as "Underboss" continues!
name: Underboss: Part Four

description: The man called Silke has inspired Wilson Fisk's lieutenants to take him out of action! But what surprising events led up to this point? And what connection is there to the contract on Matt Murdock's life? Brian Michael Bendis and Alex Maleev reveal the Kingpin's Judas as "Underboss" continues!
name: Underboss: Part Five

description: We're sworn to secrecy about the plot of this issue ? but it will change Daredevil's life forever! Remember when hot writer Brian Michael Bendis asked us not to reveal anything about ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN #13? This one's even bigger!
name: Underboss: Part Six

description: The FBI steps in to sort out the remains of the Kingpin's crime empire ? and their investigations may change Daredevil's life forever!
name: Out

description: Part 1 of the comic bok adaptation of the 1981 fantasy film.
Part two of the movie adaptation.

The Inhumans are attacked by the Doombots while Reed Richards goes in search of the X- Men¹s mutant-locator, Cerebro! Meanwhile, Captain America comes face to face with his new partner, the all-new, all-unkillable Daredevil! Featuring the untold origin of the Asgardians and Thor¹s epic battle against the Frost Giants! Plus: the triumphant return of the Star Jammers, and the fate of Wolverine!
name: Chapter Five

description: Behold the formation of the all-new, all-different X-Men! But in a world where there are no humans to protect or to hate and fear them, what use is there for the Children of the Atom? Meanwhile, Captain America and Daredevil follow the Skull¹s growing forces as they move across the country to New York! Plus: Hulk and the new Defenders finalize their plans to contact Captain Mar-Vell from beyond the grave! And, Tony Stark reveals, at last, why he¹s in business with the Goblin!
name: Chapter Six

description: The Hulk enters death¹s realm as the search begins for the slain soul of Captain Marvel! And what greets him will rock the foundation of the "new" Defenders! Also, Captain America begins his defense against the coming forces of the Skull! Meanwhile, Reed Richards' redesign of the X-Men¹s Cerebro helmet continues as he is reunited with the Thing and meets the Brothers Grimm! And on the surface of the moon, John Jameson makes a terrible discovery!
name: Chapter Seven

description: The secret of the mutation of Earth is revealed against the backdrop of an even bigger mystery: the truth behind the universe itself! The battle for New York begins as Spider-Man's daughter, Venom, takes on the Iron Maiden in Times Square while Clea, the Sorceress Supreme, clashes with Thor, the Goddess of Thunder! Meanwhile, Luna of the Inhumans makes a terrible self-discovery! Plus: Captain America recruits the World Super Powers?but why? And last but not least, it's the Skull vs. the Goblin for leadership of America!
name: Chapter Eight

description: Revelations packed issue! Discover the identity of the being who caused the mutation of everyone on Earth! Gasp in shock when Reed Richards learns why there are heroes at all! Shriek in surprise as Captain America uncovers the tragic demise of Excalibur! Break out in a cold sweat when you witness the final fate of the Green Goblin! And risk going mad as the Skull stakes his claim to America!
name: Chapter Nine

description: It's all-out war against the Skull as Captain America returns to New York with an army comprised of the leaders of the World Super Powers, including King Britain, Sunfire, the seven Silver Samurai, Black Widow, The Black Knight, Ka-Zar and Colossus! Plus: Learn how the Watcher went blind!
name: Chapter Ten

description: On Earth, it's all of the surviving heroes vs. the Skull! On the moon, the knowledge of humanity's purpose leads to an all-out war between Black Bolt and the Celestials! Meanwhile, Jean Grey confronts her husband Wolverine! Plus: Tony Stark, X-51 and the Man-Wolf all appear as we approach the finale!
name: Chapter Eleven

description: The Celestials have finally come to destroy the Earth. For Tony Stark it is his last chance to show that he is not a traitor to his race. Turning his Mansion into a massive Iron Man mech, Tony rushes headfirst into battle against The Celestials, who are able to easily deflect his attacks, realizing he doesn't have much time before The Celestials decide to utterly annihilate him Tony races directly at The One Above All and slams into the Celestial Emperor's chest. He fails to do any damage to The One Above All however and dies shortly after emerging from the ruins of his Mansion and sees The Silver Surfers attacking Jemiah the Analyzer. It is then that Galactus (Franklin Richards) appears and prepares for his confrontation with The Celestials.
name: Chapter Twelve

description:
After the events of last issue Galactus (Franklin Richards) has arrived on Earth and is planning to destroy the unborn Celestial growing inside of Earth's core...much to the displeasure of The Fifth Celestial Host who were already in New York when he arrived. As Galactus tries to set up his machine he comes under attack from The Celestials and thankfully is protected by his Heralds: Norrin Radd and Shalla Bal. It is not long before the Atlanteans join in the fight and it is during this time that Nezarr the Calculator murders Shalla Bal.

Enraged by the loss of Shalla Bal, Galactus kills Nezarr and then Gammenon the Gather who tries beating Galactus to death with his Gathering Rod. The resulting explosion created by Gammenon's death knocks Galactus out and it is then that The Asgardians who believed Loki when he told them that they were not truly Gods come to face off against their true creators.

But it ends in disaster as Arishem the Judge forces the Asgardians to believe they all are dead with the exception of Loki who is trying to fight their manipulative telepathic hold over him. Galactus recovers while The Celestials attention is focused on Loki and takes out Jemiah the Analyzer and Eson the Searcher. This prompts the other Celestials to flee while they still can but there is still a problem.

Galactus has expended too much energy during his fight with The Celestials and must feed. Reed Richards, the former Mr. Fantastic and the father of this Galactus, begs him not to destroy Earth. However inside Richards is filled with anguish as he cannot even tell his own son that he is Galactus lest he wishes for The Celestials to become the Masters of Creation.

Galactus agrees not to destroy Earth and just removes the unborn Celestial instead. Ascending into the Heavens, Galactus says his goodbyes and tells Reed that they will not meet again. Sometime later after the first "Human Torch" has been constructed, Captain America makes a speech about how Humanity will never again let other races like The Celestials subjegate and manipulate them ever again. Also Reed sees a vision of the Captain Mar-Vell/Captain Universe composite entity known as "Marvel Universe" who tells him that he is going to be reborn and that all that has just happened is only the beginning of something much larger.
name: Issue X

description:
As the Original Quest begins [reprinted w/colors added] the humans have captured Redlance and have begun to torture him in preparation for sacrificing him to their god, Gotara. A brief history flashback tells the bare-bones story of how the high-ones came to The World of Two Moons and how the humans reacted in fear and hatred, killing many of them. An artistic segue of two of the High Ones, morphs into Cutter & Skywise as they assess the situation.

Cutter leads the males of his tribe to rescue Redlance, killing the human Tabak before he can murder the gentle tracker. On his way out of the human village with Redlance slung over Nightrunner's back, Cutter delivers a warning to the human Spirit-Man to leave them alone and the Wolfriders return to their woodland holt, Goodtree's Rest.

As the elves do what little they can to heal Redlance and ease his pain, the Spirit-Man encourages the human villagers to pursue the elves into the forest and burn it down to cleanse it of the "demon" infestation. Despite Cutter's assertation that burning the forest will be just as bad for the human tribe as for the WolfRider tribe, the Spirit-Man still sets the forest afire.

So, the elves are forced to invade the caverns of the trolls. This issue concludes as Picknose leads Cutter and his tribe to the troll-king, Greymung the Shiftless.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

In an article from Archie Goodwin he admits his chagrin at being one of the Marvel editors who turned the Pinis away when they first started publishing the title and apologizes. In this essay it is revealed that the new colors for the interiors have been provided by Glynis Wein.
name: Fire And Flight

first_appearance_teams.name: Humans of the World of Two Moons

team_credits.name: Humans of the World of Two Moons

description:
As the tribe approaches the throne-room of Greymung the Shiftless we "meet" all 17 members of the tribe (though not the 14 wolves).

After meeting with Greymung the WolfRiders prepare for council, Greymung strikes Skywise because of this fascination with the large magnet Greymung has been using as a footstool; apparently the stone is "sacred" and fell from the sky. In lieu of gutting Greymung, Cutter uses the pommel of New Moon to break off a chunk of the rock, gifting Skywise with his own lodestone.

Next Greymung instructs Picknose to escort the WolfRiders to the Tunnel of Golden Light, assuring the elves that if his kind could handle sunlight, they'd love the land at the end of the tunnel. Assuming that Greymung wouldn't betray them since this is a good way to get them out of his caverns, the WolfRiders go excitedly. The journey takes a couple of days, but when they get there and investigate the source of the Golden Light, Picknose escapes Treestump, who was set to guard him, and causes the tunnel to collapse, stranding the night-dwelling elves in a desert the likes of which they'd never imagined.

As they contemplate their doom, the "secret" of the lodestone (its' compass-like property) is discovered. Now that they will be able to tell direction, they decide to follow Skywise's lodestone into the burning waste. On the second night, Redlance, still wounded grievously from his encounter with the humans, falls; Nightfall stays with her lovemate. The next night, they arrive at the foothills, and after an encounter with a cactus, discover the moisture-storing capability of these "prickly" plants.

Skywise contemplates his sunburn and Cutter goes in search of better sustenance and shelter for his tribe and ♦calls♦ Skywise to see something amazing. An elfin village...

[we see the village, but no individuals in this issue...]
name: Journey to Sorrow's End

description:
Skywise goes to see what has Cutter so excited and sees a village. Of Elves. "Just like us" he says, but Cutter says "not like us" and, remembering the cruelty of the humans and the treachery of the trolls, decides that his tribe will TAKE what they need from these strange brown-skinned elves.

So, the WolfRiders raid the village of Sun-Folk; Cutter unable to help himself, kidnaps the green-eyed beauty and the tribe escapes back up into the hills. They are pursued by several, but only Rayek actually makes it up to where they watch their pursuers. Rayek uses his magic to stun Pike and the others tackle and bind/blindfold him.

Leetah asks why they can't see that elves help elves and she and Rayek take the tribe to face her father, The Sun-toucher. As the village reluctantly but with growing enthusiasm, welcomes the WolfRiders, Cutter heads back to fetch Redlance and Nightfall, accompanied by Rayek and Leetah. Leetah heals Redlance and they all return to the village.

As the two groups of elves introduce themselves the Sunfolk lead the WolfRiders to their Mother of Memory who explains that their name for these hills is ALSO Sorrow's End...
name: Raid at Sorrow's End

person_credits.name: Wendy Pini
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description:
Savah delivers a brief history of the village and assures the WolfRiders and their cubs that here, there are NO HUMANS.

The two tribes begin to assimilate but as Leetah continues to deny Recognition, Cutter is still drawn to her, making Rayek madly jealous. ShenShen tells Leetah she should follow her heart and Rayek chastises her. Soon after, Rayek issues the Challenge of Hand, Head and Heart, a competition that will allow one of them to solely "woo" Leetah.

Savah explains what the Challenge is, Skywise loans his lodestone to Cutter (for luck), and the two begin the trial of Hand, a balancing wrestle while blindfolded, and despite his confidence, Rayek loses to Cutter.

Next comes the trial of Head, a battle of wits, which Rayek is more confident of winning and is sure that though he has no change to win all three of the trials now, Leetah will be more impressed by cunning than physical prowess, anyway...

So both contestants are stripped of their weapons, blindfolded and bound, and led into the caves in the mountains surrounding the village...
name: The Challenge

person_credits.name: Wendy Pini
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description:
Cutter wriggles loose from his bonds, and using his acute sense of smell, follows his nose to New Moon, his sword. It's been dropped into a crevice. As he ponders HOW to get it out, the lodesone's magnetic property attaches itself to the sword.

At the same time, Rayek uses a handy sharp rock to cut his bonds, and uses his tracking skill to see where his fellow SunFolk have hidden his golden blade. He finds it in a similar crevice and uses his necklace to pull it out and returns to the village, certain that the barbarian Cutter has lost to find the WolfRider waiting for him. He cries foul, that using the lodestone was magic, but Savah overrules him and Cutter is declared winner of the trial of Hand and Head.

Next, comes the trial of Heart. Savah soul-searches the two contestants to find their true fear. Certain that his is the danger of this tribe, Savah finds his true phobia, then Rayeks and they all congregate at the Bridge of Destiny to begin Cutter's trial of Heart.

The WolfRiders are confused by this fear of heights, but Cutter explains that this is a LONG fall and certain death lies at its end. He's to walk across the Bridge of Destiny, touch the sun design at its end and return. He ventures out onto the Bridge, but collapses with fear. A boastful Rayek struts out onto the Bridge to show how HE's not afraid of heights, but is nearly blown off the bridge, catching hold with bloody fingers, dangling above a death-fall. Cutter's protective instincts kick in and, despite his fear, he ventures back onto the Bridge and pulls Rayek to safety. Rayek leaves in a huff as Cutter clings to the Bridge in fear. Savah explains that Rayek has lost as his fear was a fear of losing and his Pride has been his downfall.

As the tribes wait, Cutter assimilates his hear, stands, walks to the end of the Bridge, touches the sun-symbol, and returns. Wins his trial of Heart, and is again put down by Leetah who reiterates that he has won the right to WOO her. He states his confusion of why woo when Recognition has "spoken" and leaves.

Later, Leetah wakes from a Recognition nightmare and follow the wolfsong to bear witness to the tribe's first Howl in the new land.
name: Bridge of Destiny

description:
All will to live leaves the chief and he send the rest of the hunters home. Cutter refuses to leave, and the two of them set off in pursuit of the monster.

They track it to its lair and lie in wait for its return, but Cutter a youth of 20, still barely more than a cub, falls asleep. Then, as if it was waiting for this, Madcoil emerges and faces off with Bearclaw. Madcoil kills Bearclaw, but Bearclaw grievously wounds it. The wounded Madcoil retreats into its lair and something wakes Cutter just in time to hold his father as he dies and to hear his last words. Bequeathed the sword New Moon and the tribe's leadership the 10th chief of the WolfRider dies.

Soon after a small pack of wolves emerges, led by Bearclaw's wolf-friend Blackfell, who carry off the corpse in the manner of the Way. As the pack leaves, Cutter asks a female wolf (Timmain?) to cry a summons for the other WolfRider hunters. By the time they arrive Cutter has a plan, and they build a large strangle-weed net. Then Cutter lures Madcoil from its lair and the tribe, as a whole, slays the monsters.

Treesump explains that though this Howl is for Bearclaw, it's really for their new chief, Cutter. Leetah, eavesdropping, comes away with a better understanding of the WolfRider tribe's faith in their young chief.

As the two tribes continue to assimilate, Leetah asks Nightfall what, exactly, a soul-name is. Suddenly, the local volcano rumbles, and Suntoucher has his new apprentice, Skywise, summon Scouter with his keen eyesight. Sure enough, the zwoots are stampeding toward the village!

The WolfRiders go to turn the stampede and maybe get fresh meat! They easily turn the herd...
name: Voice of the Sun

description:
Having turned the zwoot herd, the WolfRiders now hunt! Cutter, Skywise and Pike capture a "small" one and deliver it to Savah, who enters its mind and the SunFolk have another.

Leetah has an epiphany but decides to wait till things calm down to share her decision.

Scouter & Dewshine have captured another (huge) zwoot, but as they relax, it gets its second wind. Scouter, caught in the ropes, goes flying. Dewshine leaps to the rescue with her dagger but is struck by the fear-maddened zwoot. Leetah, unthinking, rushes in to save her. The zwoot is killed by the WorfRider archers (One-Eye and Strongbow).

Cutter begs Leetah to heal his little cousin, bargaining the offer of leaving it she'll just save Dewshine. Leetah snaps at him and carries the young female into her hut for healing. After she recovers a bit from the healing, Leetah notices Cutter's absence and tracks him down. As they begin to argue, she says his soulname, Tam, aloud and suddenly she knows what a soulname is and that she's accepted Cutter as her mate. Before they can share the good news, Nightrunner runs off with her on his back.

In the hills surrounding Sorrow's End, Rayek has witnessed the zwoot hunt and Savah send her spirit out to let him know that Leetah has chosen. Rayek sets off into the burning waste to find his own sorrow's end.

That night Cutter and Leetah finally answer the call of Recognition to be discovered the next morning by her father, SunToucher. In an act of foreshadowing, while Leetah and Cutter consummate their relationship and the rest of the elves revel, Savah "sends out" her consciousness into the void, searching for she-knows-not-what, something frightens her back to her handmaiden, Ahdri.
name: Soul Names

deck: Cutter begins his first real QUEST for the other tribes of the Children of the High Ones...
description:
It's been seven years since Leetah & Cutter finally gave in to their Recognition and consummated their relationship. In the interim Nightrunner, Cutter's wolf-friend, has lost his place as the pack leader of the wolves that came with the WolfRiders from the Holt and is nearing his dotage. Cutter has been out hunting rabbits for his friend and as he returns to his home for the night his cubs, Ember & Suntop, greet him enthusiastically.

Their questions prompt flashbacks to their birth. Shenshen, as the village midwife, tried to bar Cutter from Leetah's birthing chamber, but Cutter (ahem) convinced her otherwise. Then shocked both tribes waiting by emerging with TWINS!

Suddenly, in the 'present', a "stingtail" (scorpion) alights on Ember's foot. Cutter contemplates how to get it off her foot without hurting her or it having a chance to sting her. Then a dagger knocks the scorpion away without killing it -- Leetah has learned knife-craft during the intermission.

Meanwhile at the rocks in the foothills near the caves where the tribe's elders have stayed, Strongbow, with his wolf-friend Briersting, is training his son Dart in archery. Suddenly, the wolf then his elf-friend catch a scent on the air they thought they'd never encounter again and call the alarm. All around the village the WolfRiders get the warning and converge on where Strongbow waits -- humans have come to Sorrow's End!

While gentle Woodlock startles his pack-mates with his savage death wish, Redlance tells Cutter he wants to hear the humans story -- and he deserves to hear it since he's the one who they tortured...

The Humans, Aro, his poor mad brother Dro and his mate Thaya, tell their story of how they came to be lost in the burning waste: the fires set by the Spirit-Man were much more destructive than anyone expected and after days of floating in the local lake finally the fires died out, leaving nothing but ash and death. The little family traveled for many days in the direction of sun-goes-down (West) and finally encountered another tribe of humans, but Dro's madness caused them to be driven out since Aro would not abandon his brother. Now, they're all dying.

Then Aro tells the tale of how the humans view the elves, as trespassers on the sacred ground created for humans by Gotara and coveted by the High Ones and when they Palace landed why the humans have tried to exterminate them for the thousands of years since...

Woodlock again encourages Cutter to kill them, to let him kill them, but when he draws his bow, he cannot kill the humans. At that point Dro collapses in death and Cutter tells the humans he'll let them leave, but to leave the corpse as a warning to any who approach that humans are NOT welcome here. So the humans wander off to die in the desert.

This enrages Strongbow, who feels that Bearclaw would have let him kill the humans and a challenge ensues. Quickly, Cutter defeats Strongbow in a battle of wills and Strongbow accepts his place, as is THE WAY.

Cutter goes to Savah for advice: if the humans are still going to come, is any place safe? And if these humans found OTHER humans, maybe there are more tribes of elves? So Cutter decides he's going on a quest: to see if he can find more of the children of the High Ones...
name: The Quest Begins

team_credits.name: Humans of the World of Two Moons

description:
Cutter tells his tribe of his impending quest and orders them all to stay put, while off to the side Leetah makes sure Skywise will be accompanying him, orders or no.

Traveling on zwoots to save their aging wolf-friends the added stress of the desert-crossing, the four friends re-cross the burning waste, guided by Skywise's lodestone and find the opening to the tunnel of golden light, which has been cleared as they suspected it would. They enter the caverns after releasing the zwoots, but there are no trolls in the troll-caverns. The forges are cold and bat-dung cakes just about everything... what has hapenned to the trolls?

They exit into the Holt forest, to find that the humans told true: there are no trees, everything is still, seven years later, still black and ash. They return to the father-tree, Goodtree's Rest, and mourn the loss of their home's beauty and their birth-sites. Cutter finds a sapling and mourns that his cubs will be fully mature before they could even climb the tree...

As they set off, there are spies watching them. Protected from the sun Picknose and Old Maggoty watch them with greedy eyes--they've returned with the sword. The two trolls coat themselves in one of Old Maggoty's brews that kills scent, sneak up (downwind) of the four and toss bags of a sleeping potion, putting both elves and one of the wolves to sleep. When the other wolf attacks, they dust him, too. They carry off the two elves and especially New Moon, Bearclaw's sword!

The two awake, groggy from being drugged, just in time for the wolves to catch up. As the two trolls prepare to re-dust the wolves and skin them !! the elves ♦send♦ to their wolves to flee until called. As Oddbit wonders just what they'll do with two elves, Picknose decides they'll be his servants -- a troll of means needs servants! As Cutter & Skywise are serving dinner to the three trolls, discussion of what a character Bearclaw was runs around to Bearclaw's likeness for Maggoty's Dreamberry Wine. Since Cutter & Skywise have no idea what "wine" is, Picknose orders them to fetch the wine and offers them a drink...
name: Return to the Holt

description:
As they all drink Dreamberry Wine, they reminisce about things. Picknose and Maggoty show Cutter and Skywise the secret of New Moon (the key hidden inside the pommel). Then, when asked, they tell what happened to the trolls of the caverns...

A brief history, once all the known trolls lived in the far north, but as the "ice-sheets" (glaciers) moved in, it got colder and colder and it got hard to find food, etc, so they moved south (to the caverns we know) but after a time, Guttlekraw and some followers wanted to return to the north for some [unknown] reason, so Greymung and some followers basically ran them off and sealed any tunnels behind them. But over the many many years, Greymung got fat and lazy and shortly after the WolfRiders were tricked through the Tunnel of Golden Light, Guttlekraw returned with an army, killing any they didn't capture. What they did with the dead is not to be mentioned (ick). But Picknose grabbed Oddbit, whom he loves, and with Maggoty, escaped into the open air and sunlight--brave troll!

When asked about the key he tells the two WolfRiders of how Two-Edge (and who Two Edge may be) whispered the secret of New Moon to him as he returned from the Tunnel of Golden Light and how he cursed his bad luck that the key to the "golden hoard" was now lost in all that sun. Then they start reminiscing about Bearclaw and Picknose makes the mistake of stating that Bearclaw would have been an excellent Troll, which enrages Cutter.

He attacks Picknose as Skywise sneaks some of Maggoty's sleep-powder and throws it at the trolls, but it has no affect, so they jump out the window ♦send♦ing for their wolf-friends. Picknose catches Skywise's shackles, but he slips out of the troll-sized cuffs, since they were clearly not made to hold elves. The four run away. Picknose isn't too terribly upset...

Cutter removes his shackles and complains that now his sword is ruined, with no pommel and Skywise shows him that he filched the pommel-key. New Moon is fixed! Then Picknose realizes the key is missing... oh no!!!
name: The Dreamberry Tale

description:
Reprints the first 3/4 or so of the 1978 ElfQuest #8:

In the village at Sorrow's End, Ember answer's the pups-call and greets her first WolfFriend, Choplicker (awwww). Later that night as the tribe meets, Leetah wonders at actually missing Cutter, he'll only be gone one year after all. Moonshade complains that her place is at her mate's side and *she* never would have stayed if Strongbow went away and Nightfall comes to Leetah's defense and states that Moonshade would, too, have stayed if she had cubs that needed her! Moonshade's come-back that the tribe would take perfectly good care of the cubs isn't answered.

In private, Leetah tells Nightfall she didn't stay for the cubs' sake, but because she was afraid of something NEW and condemns herself as a coward.

Back in the woods near where the old Holt was, Cutter catches a mount for himself. Nightrunner is disgruntled that Cutter will ride another mount. Cutter tells him that his paws are too raw (both wolves have bandages around their paws now), he's old and besides, the first of the creatures they caught kicked him [Nightrunner] in the eye when he bit it in the rump, and he can barely see. After all, these creatures are for riding, not eating! Commenting that these creatures (horses?) look like smaller no-humped versions of the zwoots, they dub them No-Humps.

So they continue on for 3 moons with no sign of any other tribes, human or elfin, and wonder if Aro lied to them, but finally they enter a bog and then see a large, dense forest. Cutter, in a good mood to see TREES rescues a drowning squirrel in the bog, which runs up his bow and bites him on the hand. In his pique, he throws the squirrel into a tree, overbalancing himself and falls into the bog, nasty water and his new rodent-bite and all.

They enter this strange dark new forest and doff their sun-gear, back to being "barbarians" again. As days pass, Cutter gets irritable and Skywise worries, until finally Cutter collapses. Skywise realizes Cutter is burning up with fever and sets off with Starjumper to find 'whistling leaf" to treat the infection. Cutter's delirium increases and while reminiscing about the cool touch and soothing heal-song of Rain, the old tribe healer [who was killed by Madcoil] he imagines he sees his father's last wolf-friend, Blackfell, and follows the apparition. He sees his parent's spirits and tells them he can't go with them, he has a family, a wonderful mate and two lovely cubs, and runs off. Seeing light in his delirium, he imagines it's the day-star and he's back in the burning waste, so he follows the light and wanders into the camp of two humans, Nonna & Adar, who take him for a child at first. Nightrunner tries to defend his friend, but gets his good eye burned and runs off to fetch Skywise.

When he attacks, they realize he's no child and Nonna calls him one of the bird-spirits that guide her people. Cutter slices a hole in the tent-wall but then collapses. Nonna tends Cutter despite his fear of her and he wonders that a human would be so tender as all the WolfRiders have ever known of humans was death.

Meanwhile, Skywise searches for the whistling-weed and Nightrunner searches for Skywise. They each find their goal at about the same time and go racing back to save Cutter from the evil humans! Just as Adar mends the hole in their tent-wall that Cutter sliced, Skywise cuts another and leaps into the dwelling to rescue his chief, but Cutter says "no"... [end of this issue]
name: Hands of the Symbol Maker

description: Inside the Tempel of the Sun, Savah maintains the rituals of worship for the Sun Villagers. She enters the solemn dream-world on a regular basis, but this time discovers a startling sinful presence. Suddenly, she stiffens into a comatose trance that neither Leetah nor Ahdri may allieviate. Only Suntop knows and understands. He looks past Savah's appearance and finds her spirit entangled with a vile presence. The only other discernible revelation Sun Top receives is that his father Cutter Kinseeker, will soon in person encounter the same evil that has paralyzed Savah, so that he must be warned.
name: The Warning And The Way

description: Cutter has journeyed a long way from Sorrow's End and his life with Leetah and the Sun Villagers. His old veteran wolf, #night runner is becoming too old. Approaching a steep precipice, his trusted bond-animal cannot follow him onward to the mysterious alure of the Blue Mountain.
name: The Lodestone

description: Olbar must rule his tribe despite numerous attempts of his local witch doctor, who is half-troll, to seize control of the public opinion. In addition to this, she enlists the services of Olbar's brother, who has had his name revoked, to steal the Lodestone that Skywise carries. Olbar has only recently made friends with Cutter the rag-tag elf adventurers seeking glory.
name: The Forbidden Grove

description: Cutter and Skywise enter the forest of endless slumber. They venture to find a great trove of hibernating animals of the forest. What else will the duo of Questing elves discover?
name: Noisybad Highthing!

description: Winnowill has suppressed the memory and child nature of Lord Voll. He is ready to punish Strongbow until he learns of the presence of Cutter & Leetah's twin son and daughter. Seeing the twins in person revives Lord Voll's faith in The High-Ones.
name: Riddle of Blue Mountain

description: A dark new villain rises to power and threaten Kro's control over the demonic Deviants.
name: The Old Priest Writ Large...!

description:
The members of X-Factor must track down and defeat an enemy within their ranks. "Grand Design" is the title of the gripping story in which one of Marvel's hottest new super-teams leaps from the pages of its own regular monthly title into an annual on its own.

The X-Factor is called to Russia by the US Government to destroy a base that is using mutants as weapons. There they realize that nothing is just like were told them, as at the airport they are attacked by mutants.

The head chief of the operation is Doppelganger, an evil mutant that uses his powers to drain other mutant's powers for himself, and he is the one who has been actually taken mutants in Russia. They kidnap Iceman and Doppelganger steals his powers. Then a group of rebels mutants lead by Blind Faith steal Bobby from Doppelganger's group.

Meanwhile, the fake Iceman joins the X-Factor. The real Iceman is in a hideout with a lot of other Russian mutants that think he is working with KGB to kill all the mutants. Then after a brief introduction of Mentac, Concussion, Iron Curtain and Sibercat, they explain the real intentions of Doppelganger to Bobby and decide to help him freed his friends.

Doppelganger disguised as Iceman lead the X-Factor into a trap inside his base where he make experiments with mutants. He uses the Crimson Dynamo to battle the X-Factor. The real Iceman and the Siberforce enter the base and release all prisoners, and then help the X-Factor to defeat Doppelganger and Crimson Dynamo.

At the end Blind Faith compelled the X-Factor to blame themselves for the misunderstood and they leave Russia thinking about the Siberforce.
name: Grand Design

description:
Quicksilver's kidnaping of Franklin Richards sends X-Factor on a desperate flight to the Moon to rescue him!  But when they arrive, instead of a young boy and his mutant captor, they encounter...the Inhumans!                                  

SPOILERS

Quicksilver under the influence of Maximus, battles X-Factor, the Inhumans, and Power Pack.       

Note: This issue was originally titled "Man On The Moon" when first solicited.
name: The Man In The Moon
